On Monday, around 600 striking employees barricaded roads leading to the site. JOHANNESBURG Police are monitoring a protest at the Kusile Power Station which has seen 25 people arrested since the demonstration started a week ago. On Monday, around 600 striking employees barricaded roads leading to the site. They are demanding better working conditions and skills development.The police s Gerald Sedibe says they will remain in the area. Police are still continuing to monitor the situation except that 25 people who were arrested on the 6th also appeared at the Witbank Magistrates Court. They were granted bail of R1,000 each. 